Lebow has run in 32 marathons, including London, Paris, Rome, Stockholm, Iceland, Seoul and Vienna.; "The most exciting thing is the start of the race," he said.
; The cities are different, but most marathons include a carbo-loading pasta party the night before, medical exams, a post-race celebration, commemorative T-shirts and awards to finishers.
Going to Bermuda, for example, costs approximately $900 from San Francisco.
; Some runs are intriguing because of current events.
